The following link is the users manual for HISAT2 containing all information on each of the different settings and arguments:
http://daehwankimlab.github.io/hisat2/manual/

The following settings were used in Cyverse to align the fastq files to the refereence genome:
maximum fragment length for valid paired-end alignments: 500
time: false
Report alignments tailored for transcript assemblers including StringTie: false
Report alignments tailored specifically for Cufflinks: false
minimum fragment length for valid paired-end alignments: 0
Genome fasta file: Mus_musculus.GRCm39.dna.toplevel.fa
FASTQ Files: (All forward and reverse fastq.gz files for 28 samples are input)
File type: PE
New format summary file: true
Number of threads: 4
Minimum intron length: 20
maximum intron length: 500000
